<p>Heroku is a container-based cloud Platform as a Service (PaaS). Developers use Heroku to deploy, manage, and scale modern apps. The platform is elegant, flexible, and easy to use, offering developers the simplest path to getting their apps to market.</p>

<p>This tutorial will teach you how to deploy your rails 6 app ot heroku.
The guide assumes that you:</p>
<ul>
  <li>are using linux ubuntu as your OS ()</li>
  <li>are using postgres as your appâ€™s database</li>
  <li>have opened an account with heroku <a href="https://www.google.com/url?sa=t&amp;rct=j&amp;q=&amp;esrc=s&amp;source=web&amp;cd=&amp;cad=rja&amp;uact=8&amp;ved=2ahUKEwiAttb4ic3tAhWUsnEKHX63D6IQFjAAegQIARAD&amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Fsignup.heroku.com%2F&amp;usg=AOvVaw2kG63H0ONIjUijpD8T5fVY" target="_blank">Create a Heroku account</a></li>
</ul>

<p>Lets begin:</p>

<h2 id="1-install-heroku-cli">1. Install heroku CLI</h2>
<section class="terminal-container terminal-fixed-top">
<header class="terminal">
<span class="button red"></span>
<span class="button yellow"></span>
<span class="button green"></span>
user@local_machine
</header>

<div class="terminal-home">
<p class="console">sudo snap install --classic heroku</p>

<h5 class="hashed"># Verify your installation</h5>
<p class="console">heroku --version</p>
  <h5 class="hashed">&nbsp; &nbsp; heroku/7.47.4 linux-x64 node-v12.16.2</h5>
</div>
</section>

<p>Getting started</p>

<h2 id="2-login-to-heroku">2. Login to Heroku</h2>
<p>After you install the CLI, run the heroku login command. Youâ€™ll be prompted to enter any key to go to your web browser to complete login. The CLI will then log you in automatically.</p>
